<section class="report-page"><div class="report-inner"><header class="report-header"><h1>02 | Validate the run and review</h1><img src="assets/brand/universal-orlando-logo.png" alt="Universal Orlando Resort"></header><section class="report-section"><div class="review-grid"><div class="review-field"><strong>Test evidence</strong><span>SIT, E2E, regression, performance, misuse and edge cases.</span><div class="worksheet-line"></div></div><div class="review-field"><strong>Run-state objectives</strong><span>Latency, availability, capacity, quality and SLOs.</span><div class="worksheet-line"></div></div><div class="review-field"><strong>Observability and drift</strong><span>Model, data, system, workflow and adoption signals.</span><div class="worksheet-line"></div></div><div class="review-field"><strong>Fallback and rollback</strong><span>Safe state, manual path, recovery time and authority.</span><div class="worksheet-line"></div></div><div class="review-field"><strong>Security, privacy and compliance</strong><span>Threats, access, retention, CCPA/GDPR and audit evidence.</span><div class="worksheet-line"></div></div><div class="review-field"><strong>Vendor / API dependency</strong><span>SLO, failure mode, data rights, portability and exit path.</span><div class="worksheet-line"></div></div><div class="review-field"><strong>Adoption evidence</strong><span>Training, retained use, standard work and user friction.</span><div class="worksheet-line"></div></div><div class="review-field"><strong>Outcome and economics</strong><span>Leading signals, realized benefit and cost-to-serve.</span><div class="worksheet-line"></div></div><div class="review-field"><strong>Incident and learning record</strong><span>What happened, response, recurrence control and owner.</span><div class="worksheet-line"></div></div><div class="review-field"><strong>Reusable asset</strong><span>Pattern, control, data product, evaluation or fast no.</span><div class="worksheet-line"></div></div></div><h2>Production disposition</h2><div class="decision-rail"><div>RELEASE</div><div>LIMIT / HOLD</div><div>ROLL BACK</div><div>RETIRE</div></div><div class="review-grid" style="margin-top:.1in"><div class="review-field"><strong>Decision and rationale</strong></div><div class="review-field"><strong>Decision authority and date</strong></div><div class="review-field"><strong>Conditions / follow-up</strong></div><div class="review-field"><strong>Next review trigger</strong></div></div><p style="font-size:7pt;color:#66758a">Candidate-created worksheet for interview discussion. It is not a representation of Universal's current process.</p></section><footer class="page-footer"><span>Russell Dudek | AI Show Integrity Review</span><span>3</span></footer></div></section></main></body></html>